KnowledgeBase.Title: Example Void compareGT 008
KnowledgeBase.RelatedFunctions: compare compareEQ compareNE compareGE compareLT compareLE

Example.Description: These examples use the compareGT function to compare two objects and return the Boolean value, true or false. The values of each object are compared to determine whether the first object is greater in value than the second object.

Syntax.Note: The uninitialized value of x is equal to #void.
The value #void is not greater than the value of the String.
